A vintage-style illustration of an ornate Victorian curiosity cabinet with dozens of small wooden drawers, each drawer slightly ajar revealing glowing crystalline objects of different colors and shapes. The cabinet stands in a warm, amber-lit study with dust motes floating in shafts of light. Each drawer has a tiny brass label plate, and some drawers cascade open like a waterfall, showing an organized hierarchy of mysterious luminescent artifacts nested within nested compartments. The scene evokes the feeling of discovering a meticulously organized collection of rare specimens, with rich mahogany wood grain textures and antique brass fixtures catching the golden light.
